liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Italy score seven minutes from the end thanks to the ever-reliable veteran Cristiana Girelli. What a super header it was to win it too. So disappointing for Argentina who matched the Italians for much of the game, but in the end they created very few chances, and if anyone deserved to sneak a winner it was the Europeans. Yet again, it's a firm favourite struggling against a lower-ranked opponent, but eventually coming up with a narrow win. Seems to be a pattern in this tournament.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FULL-TIME: Italy 1 - 0 Argentina

children.content: Italy score seven minutes from the end thanks to the ever-reliable veteran
Cristiana Girelli. What a super header it was to win it too.
So disappointing for Argentina who matched the Italians for much of the game, but in the end they created very few chances, and if anyone deserved to sneak a winner it was the Europeans.
Yet again, it's a firm favourite struggling against a lower-ranked opponent, but eventually coming up with a narrow win. Seems to be a pattern in this tournament.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: They've finally broken through, via the veteran Cristiana Girelli! She lept high to meet the floating cross from the left from Boattin and used every neck muscle to direct it into the top corner. Great header, and probably deserved for Italy.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 87' GOAAAAAAAAL Italy!

children.content: They've finally broken through, via the veteran Cristiana Girelli!
She lept high to meet the floating cross from the left from Boattin and used every neck muscle to direct it into the top corner.
Great header, and probably deserved for Italy.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: You don't get a much more entertaining 0-0 than that. Italy have tried to dominate the ball but Argentina never let them get particularly comfortable. We've seen both sides intent on attacking, with Giacinti looking in the mood up front for Italy and Tefi Banini popping up everywhere for Argentina. There has been a fair bit of niggle too. What more could you want? Goals, I suppose.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: Italy 0 - 0  Argentina

children.content: You don't get a much more entertaining 0-0 than that. Italy have tried to dominate the ball but Argentina never let them get particularly comfortable. We've seen both sides intent on attacking, with Giacinti looking in the mood up front for Italy and Tefi Banini popping up everywhere for Argentina.
There has been a fair bit of niggle too.
What more could you want? Goals, I suppose.
